   <concept id="FAR_22_1903"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">22.1903</ph> Applicability.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1483e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1505e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  This subpart applies to contracts
covered by the Service Contract Labor Standards statute (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41
U.S.C. chapter 67</xref>, formerly known as the Service Contract
Act, <xref href="Subpart_22.10.dita#FAR_Subpart_22_10"
                        base="i1096345"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  22.10</xref>),
or the Wage Rate Requirements (Construction) statute (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">40 U.S.C. chapter 31, Subchapter	IV</xref>,
formerly known as the Davis Bacon Act, <xref href="Subpart_22.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_22_4"
                        base="i1097644"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  22.4</xref>), that require
performance in whole or in part within the United States . When
performance is in part within and in part outside the United States,
this subpart applies to the part of the contract that is performed
within the United States.</p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1505e27" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d1483e44" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1505e32" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        This
subpart applies to workers as defined at <xref href="22.1901.dita#FAR_22_1901"
                              base="i1095243"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.1901</xref>. As provided in
that definition-</p>
                     <ol id="d1483e61" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1505e41" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              Workers are covered regardless
of the contractual relationship alleged to exist between the contractor
or subcontractor and the worker;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1505e46" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              Workers
with disabilities whose wages are calculated pursuant to special
certificates issued under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">29 U.S.C.	214(c)</xref> are
covered; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1505e54" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              Workers
who are registered in a bona fide apprenticeship program or training
program registered with the Department of Labor’s Employment and
Training Administration, Office of Apprenticeship, or with a State Apprenticeship
Agency recognized by the Office of Apprenticeship, are covered.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1505e59" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        This subpart
does not apply to-</p>
                     <ol id="d1483e108" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1505e65" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA)-covered
individuals performing in connection with contracts covered by the E.O.,
i.e., those individuals who perform duties necessary to the performance
of the contract, but who are not directly engaged in performing
the specific work called for by the contract, and who spend less
than 20 percent of their hours worked in a particular workweek performing
in connection with such contracts;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1505e70" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              Individuals
exempted from the minimum wage requirements of the FLSA under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">29	U.S.C.
213(a)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">214(a) and	(b)</xref>, unless
otherwise covered by the Service Contract Labor Standards statute
or the Wage Rate Requirements (Construction) statute. These individuals
include but are not limited to-</p>
                           <ol id="d1483e133" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d1505e82" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    Learners, apprentices,
or messengers whose wages are calculated pursuant to special certificates
issued under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                                          format="html"
                                          scope="external"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">29 U.S.C. 214(a)</xref>;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d1505e90" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    Students
whose wages are calculated pursuant to special certificates issued
under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                          format="html"
                                          scope="external"
                                          class="- topic/xref "> 29 U.S.C. 214(b)</xref>;
and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d1505e98" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    Those employed
in a bona fide executive, administrative, or professional capacity <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/"
                                          format="html"
                                          scope="external"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">(29
U.S.C.	213(a)(1)</xref> and <ph outputclass="CFR" class="- topic/ph ">29 CFR part
541</ph>); or
                                 </p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1505e109">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              Seasonal recreational
services or seasonal recreational equipment rental for the general
public on Federal lands, except for lodging and food services associated
with seasonal recreational services, in accordance with <xref href="https://www.federalregister.gov/executive-order/13838"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">Executive Order 13838</xref>,
Exemption from <xref href="https://www.federalregister.gov/executive-order/13658"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">Executive Order 13658</xref> for
Recreational Services on Federal Lands (3 CFR, 2018 Comp., p. 831),
as implemented by the U.S. Department of Labor regulations at <xref href="https://www.federalregister.gov/select-citation/2020/10/23/29-CFR-10.4"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">29 CFR 10.4</xref>(g).
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1505e123" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  Agency
Labor Advisors, as defined at <xref href="22.001.dita#FAR_22_001"
                        base="i1098436"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">22.001</xref>,
are listed at <xref href="http://wdol.gov"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">http://wdol.gov</xref>, and are available
to provide guidance and assistance with the application of this
subpart.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
